<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A type of camera which lacks a separate veiwfinder, a mirror arrangement being used to cast the image coming through the lens <a title="Aperture" href="Aperture">aperture</a> up to the eyepiece. Such cameras allow the photogapher to see exactly how the image is likely to appear on the film, at least as far as focusing is concerned. Usually abbreviated <a title="SLR" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/SLR">SLR</a>. 
</p>
